The paper deals with lower bounds on the number of integer variables needed to describe classical combinatorial optimization problems using mixed-integer programs. This involves topics such as polytopes, extended formulations, and approximation algorithms, which are commonly studied in computer science subfields such as data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), graph theory (cs.GT), operations research (cs.OC), and machine learning (cs.LG).
